parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed Repair of Takata Airbag Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the Takata airbag recall can lead to a life-threatening situation, as the faulty airbag inflator can rupture and cause serious injury or death.
symptoms: as the issue is related to a potential failure of the airbag system in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Drainage and Faulty Bluetooth Module
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty Bluetooth module can cause the battery to drain, leading to the vehicle not starting, which can leave the driver stranded and potentially cause safety risks.
symptoms: the battery needs to be replaced frequently (every six months)
the vehicle requires multiple attempts to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to catch fire, which can lead to serious safety risks and potential damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: the fire starts from the headlight area
the fire department needs to be called to put out the fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injury or even death, as it compromises the safety of the occupants.
symptoms: Airbag failure to deploy in a crash
no warning signs or indicators prior to the failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to properly notify owners of a recall on the airbag system can lead to a lack of trust in the manufacturer and potentially put occupants at risk.
symptoms: uncertainty about the status of the airbag repair
lack of trust in the manufacturer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of power and slow acceleration can lead to accidents or difficulty navigating roadways, potentially causing harm to occupants or other road users.
symptoms: Vehicle moves slowly when pulling off

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wind Noise and Plastic Sound from Driver's Side Window
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The wind noise and plastic sound from the driver's side window can be a distraction to the driver, potentially leading to accidents or decreased safety.
symptoms: Wind noise and plastic sound from the driver's side window when driving at speeds over 20 miles per hour.
